parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair for Airbag Inflator Defect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the airbag inflator defect can lead to a potentially life-threatening situation, as the inflator may rupture during deployment, causing metal fragments to pass through the airbag and into the vehicle interior, resulting in injury or death to vehicle occupants.
symptoms: No symptoms are reported
as the issue is related to a potential failure of the airbag system in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become unable to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls
the transmission warning light is illuminated
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The power loss and engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the engine stalls
the engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle surges or accelerates unexpectedly
the power steering fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch and Transmission Hydraulic System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become unable to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the transmission warning light is illuminated
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Stabilitrak and Traction Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Stabilitrak and traction control system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The "Service Stabilitrak" warning appears
the traction control system warning appears
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle decelerates unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, making it challenging to control the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering fails intermittently
the steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle makes a grinding or winding noise
the power steering pump leaks fluid
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
and the vehicle's speed affects the power steering's performance.
